item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: Renewed interest surrounding the death of Steve Irwin has emerged as fans remember the Crocodile Hunter on the 16th anniversary of his tragic passing. Explore More The Australian zookeeper was killed on Sept. 4, 2006 after he was stung by a stingray off of the Great Barrier Reef. Irwin’s biographer, Tommy Donovan, has previously revealed that the entire incident was caught on tape. According to Donovan, the video captures the moment when Irwin pulls the stingray’s barb from his chest before he loses consciousness and subsequently dies.

item.title: Why is there a green spot on my nail?
item.author: youremail@domain.com (Some Person)
item.description: Answer Mold is caused by fungus, whereas green spots are caused by bacteria, with one strain of the bacterium “pseudomonas” being responsible for the vast majority of green nails being found virtually everywhere — on plants and animals, in soil, and even in bodies of water. When the nail becomes green, we see something like this.” Schoon tells us that green spots are not produced by dampness, as many people believe it is.
